                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony/edit/master/knpu/extra-doctrine-collections/saving-inverse-side-collection.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Back on the main part of the site, click one of the genuses, and then click one
of the users that studies it. This page has a little edit button: click that.
Welcome to a very simple <code>User</code> form.</p>
<h2 id="building-the-field">Building the Field <a class="headerlink" href="saving-inverse-side-collection#building-the-field" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Ok, same plan: add checkboxes so that I can choose which genuses are being studied
by this <code>User</code>. Open the controller: <code>UserController</code> and find <code>editAction()</code>:</p>
