</p>
<p>That's it.</p>
<p>Try it! Refresh! Cool! This <code>User</code> is studying five genuses: good for them!
Let's uncheck one genus, check a new one and hit Update.</p>
<h2 id="it-didn-t-work-inverse-relationships-are-read-only">It didn't Work!!! Inverse Relationships are Read-Only <a class="headerlink" href="saving-inverse-side-collection#it-didn-t-work-inverse-relationships-are-read-only" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Wait! It didn't work! The checkboxes just reverted back! What's going on!?</p>
<p><em>This</em> is the moment where someone who doesn't know what we're about to learn,
starts to <em>hate</em> Doctrine relations.</p>
<p>Earlier, we talked about how every relationship has two sides. You can start with
a <code>Genus</code> and talk about the genus scientist users related to it:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="b95e4ae530">
